# Department & User Management System (Java Swing MVC)

A lightweight desktop application to manage university departments, users (students, staff, admins) and HOD assignments.  
Built as a semester project to demonstrate **clean MVC separation**, **Java Swing GUI**, and **simple persistence** to a flat-file.

| **Tech Stack** | |
|----------------|----------------------------------------------|
| Language       | Java 17 (or later) |
| GUI            | Swing |
| Architecture   | MVC + Service layer |
| Persistence    | Plain-text (`departments.txt`) |
| Build Tool     | NetBeans project / javac |

---

## ✨ Key Features
* **Create / edit departments** – name & HOD in an editable table.
* **Add users** – students, staff, or admins; optional department assignment.
* **Assign / update HOD** – promotes staff to *HOD* role automatically.
* **View lists** – sortable tables for users and departments.
* **Auto-save on exit** – shutdown hook writes changes to `departments.txt`.
* **Seed data** – starter users/departments loaded at first run for a quick demo.

